{
  "texts": [
    "Because of the zero mass at 0 vehicles and a relatively low mass at high vehicle counts, the (zero-truncated) Poisson distribution does not appear to be a good representation of the data.",
    "Therefore, we formulate the prediction problem as multiclass classification.",
    "To avoid a heavily unbalanced classification problem we aggregate all cases of three or more vehicles into one group.",
    "The three resulting levels are denoted as 1, 2 and 3+.",
    "We proceed as follows:"
  ]
}